            "created": "20180215004505878",
            "text": "Everytime the macro is called as `<<uuid>>`, it creates a  RFC4122 version 4 compliant string whose chance of repeating in another instance is astronomically small. 

Remember: Macrocall doesn't store the id. It means a new id will be created for every refresh.

